# .dockerignore - Exclude unnecessary files from Docker build context
# This improves build performance and reduces image size

# Build artifacts
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/artifacts/
**/out/
**/publish/

# IDE files
**/.vs/
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/
**/*.user
**/*.suo
**/*.sln.docstates

# Test results
**/TestResults/
**/test-results/
**/*.trx
**/*.coverage

# Documentation (not needed in container)
**/docs/
**/*.md
!**/README.md

# Git
**/.git/
**/.gitignore
**/.gitattributes

# Docker files themselves
**/Dockerfile*
**/.dockerignore
**/docker-compose*.yml

# CI/CD
**/.github/
**/.azure/
**/.gitlab-ci.yml
**/azure-pipelines.yml

# Logs
**/*.log
**/logs/

# Temporary files
**/tmp/
**/temp/
**/*.tmp
**/*.cache

# OS files
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/desktop.ini

# Node modules (if any)
**/node_modules/
**/package-lock.json
**/yarn.lock

# NuGet packages (will be restored)
**/packages/
**/*.nupkg

# Scripts (not needed in container)
**/scripts/
!**/scripts/build-images.ps1

# Migration files (if not needed at runtime)
# Uncomment if migrations run separately
# **/Migrations/
